Vol / Page:  229
Edition:
Quote:  Banks' next misdemeanour was his use of the term 'Maori PT' (Maori physical training) in Parliament... The Speaker, Peter Tapsell, came to Banks' defence, pointing out that both Maori and pakeha working in his shearing shed regularly used the term and that Banks' use of it had not harmed race relations.
